Class ReflectionCloningStrategy

java.lang.Object
  com.googlecode.transloader.clone.reflect.ReflectionCloningStrategy
All Implemented Interfaces:
CloningStrategy
public final class ReflectionCloningStrategy
extends Object
implements CloningStrategy

A CloningStrategy that uses Java Reflection as its mechanism. Can clone whole object graphs or just necessary parts depending on how it is configured.

Author:
Jeremy Wales

ReflectionCloningStrategy

                                 InstantiationStrategy instantiator,
                                 CloningStrategy fallbackCloningStrategy)
Contructs a new ReflectionCloningStrategy with its dependencies injected.

Parameters:
cloningDecisionStrategy - the strategy by which the decision to clone or not to clone a particular given object is made
instantiator - the strategy by which to use instantiate normal objects (as opposed to arrays, for which standard reflection is always adequate)
fallbackCloningStrategy - the CloningStrategy to fall back to when this strategy fails
Method Detail

cloneObjectUsingClassLoader

public Object cloneObjectUsingClassLoader(Object original,
                                          ClassLoader targetClassLoader)
                                   throws Exception
Clones the given object using the given ClassLoader.

This implementation uses CyclicReferenceSafeTraverser to sucessfully handle cyclic references in the given object graph.

Specified by:
cloneObjectUsingClassLoader in interface CloningStrategy
Parameters:
original - the original object to be cloned
targetClassLoader - the ClassLoader by which to load Classes for clones
Returns:
a completely or partially cloned object graph, depending on the CloningDecisionStrategy injected in ReflectionCloningStrategy(CloningDecisionStrategy, InstantiationStrategy, CloningStrategy), with potentially the original itself being the top-level object in the graph returned if it was not cloned
Throws:
Exception - can throw any Exception depending on the implementation
